author: National Geographic
description:
The leadership of North Korea has been in the hands of one family for over seventy years, claiming a divine right to rule over the isolated country. But when Kim Jong-un disappeared for three weeks, instability rocked the dictatorship with no succession plan in place. Who would be the next in line?

Inside North Korea: The Next Leader | S1, E1
